{"parentUuid":"677f9f90-4162-4198-b5e2-e096df9461c6","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/tmp","sessionId":"80255629-0260-490a-a9b2-8fe4eeb57b63","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"as  a zsh-user how do i get the color-thingies correct? what i see from git diff:\n\n```\n\u001b[1mdiff --git i/scripts/clog.sh w/scripts/clog.sh\u001b[m\n\u001b[1mindex 5c5ff12..ae09c96 100755\u001b[m\n\u001b[1m--- i/scripts/clog.sh\u001b[m\n\u001b[1m+++ w/scripts/clog.sh\u001b[m\n\u001b[36m@@ -1,6 +1,10 @@\u001b[m\n #!/usr/bin/env bash\u001b[m\n\u001b[31m-# Show recent commits from both claude repos\u001b[m\n \u001b[m\n\u001b[31m-claude-dotfiles log --oneline --stat -20 >/tmp/clog.txt\u001b[m\n```\n\nwith `\u001b[1m`-everywhere\n\n"},"uuid":"49496e98-49c9-42c0-86a9-0e3020566ce3","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:15:05.231Z","permissionMode":"default"}
{"parentUuid":"49496e98-49c9-42c0-86a9-0e3020566ce3","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/tmp","sessionId":"80255629-0260-490a-a9b2-8fe4eeb57b63","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EVqBfrvLJP6ffiFNbLsaqJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is seeing raw ANSI escape codes in their git diff output instead of actual colors. The `[1m`, `[31m`, `[36m`, etc. are ANSI color codes that aren't being interpreted by their terminal/pager.\n\nThis is a common issue. The most likely cause is that the pager (usually `less`) isn't being told to interpret ANSI escape codes. By default, `less` needs the `-R` flag to render colors.\n\nLet me give them the fix.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3926,"cache_read_input_tokens":31168,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3926},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYfBYkPCjHc52hitUV7z1","type":"assistant","uuid":"b5402adc-a65f-44e8-a652-647462a01dc3","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:15:10.079Z"}
{"parentUuid":"b5402adc-a65f-44e8-a652-647462a01dc3","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/tmp","sessionId":"80255629-0260-490a-a9b2-8fe4eeb57b63","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EVqBfrvLJP6ffiFNbLsaqJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `[1m`, `[31m`, etc. are ANSI escape codes that your pager (`less`) isn't interpreting. Fix it by telling git to pass `-R` to less:\n\n```zsh\ngit config --global core.pager \"less -R\"\n```\n\nOr if you want it even cleaner (raw control chars + no line-wrap):\n\n```zsh\ngit config --global core.pager \"less -FRX\"\n```\n\n- `-R` — interpret ANSI color codes\n- `-F` — quit immediately if output fits on one screen\n- `-X` — don't clear the screen on exit\n\nIf that still doesn't work, check if `LESS` env var is overriding things. Add this to your `~/.zshrc`:\n\n```zsh\nexport LESS=\"-R\"\n```"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3926,"cache_read_input_tokens":31168,"output_tokens":323,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3926,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CYfBYkPCjHc52hitUV7z1","type":"assistant","uuid":"69df93ec-7850-48c5-affd-7ddebfe18f4a","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:15:13.644Z"}
