{"parentUuid":"1a3475ee-b1ea-4e41-9e0b-876a5e2ebcd6","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/tmp","sessionId":"80255629-0260-490a-a9b2-8fe4eeb57b63","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QCybxS3ixajjgRHDD7YKMA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user's git pager is set to `nvim -R` (neovim in read-only mode). That's why they're seeing raw escape codes — neovim doesn't interpret ANSI escape codes the same way `less` does in this context.\n\nThey have a few options:\n1. Switch the pager to `less -FRX`\n2. Keep nvim but configure it to handle ANSI codes (using AnsiEsc plugin or similar)\n3. Use delta or other diff tools\n\nLet me give them the straightforward answer.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":415,"cache_read_input_tokens":35094,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":415},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYfBqheikaKiqNPzoKEY1","type":"assistant","uuid":"b2c8a40c-8766-4ff2-88b9-9dde087886d0","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:19:01.949Z"}
{"parentUuid":"b2c8a40c-8766-4ff2-88b9-9dde087886d0","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/tmp","sessionId":"80255629-0260-490a-a9b2-8fe4eeb57b63","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QCybxS3ixajjgRHDD7YKMA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There it is — your pager is `nvim -R`, and neovim doesn't interpret ANSI escape codes by default.\n\nTwo options:\n\n**Option 1: Switch to less** (simplest)\n```zsh\ngit config --global core.pager \"less -FRX\"\n```\n\n**Option 2: Keep nvim but make it handle ANSI codes**\n\nAdd to your neovim config (`init.lua`):\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"TermOpen\", {\n  callback = function() vim.opt_local.number = false end,\n})\n```\n\nAnd change the pager to pipe through nvim's terminal mode:\n```zsh\ngit config --global core.pager \"nvim -R -c 'set ft=diff'\"\n```\n\nSetting `ft=diff` tells neovim to use its own diff syntax highlighting instead of relying on ANSI codes. That's the real fix if you want to stick with nvim — let neovim do the coloring rather than trying to interpret git's ANSI output."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":415,"cache_read_input_tokens":35094,"output_tokens":390,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":415,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CYfBqheikaKiqNPzoKEY1","type":"assistant","uuid":"a0f8d264-1481-4d47-ae4f-dfedd3e0fb31","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:19:06.164Z"}
